description:
A presentation covering the DAP2 data model as it relates to the Open Geospatial Consortium (OGC) abstract specifaction. Presented at the 2012 OGC Technical Committee meeting in Austin, TX.&nbsp; 
  Summary:&nbsp;  
 The presentation outlines the Data Access Protocol version 2 (DAP2) data model and its relation to servers, coverages, and various types of grids, using examples such as UGrid work with NOAA. It explains that the data model encompasses variables, operations, and datasets, with servers implementing these operations and providing additional features. DAP2 is described as domain-neutral, intended to be a lower level in a multi-tier protocol stack, compatible with standards like COARDS and CF. The data model includes variables with syntactic and semantic metadata, operations for data extraction, and servers offering web interfaces. Coverages and grids, including quadrilateral grids, are supported within the DAP2 framework, with potential for representing other types like hexagonal grids and Thiessen polygons using additional attribute information. The presentation highlights the domain-neutral design's benefits for interoperability and leveraging application-specific standards.

